# =============================================================================
# LOCAL / DEVELOPMENT
# =============================================================================
# Use a dedicated Supabase *dev* project (recommended), or local Postgres.
# Never use production DATABASE_URL or prod Supabase keys on your laptop unless
# you are intentionally debugging production (not recommended).

# PostgreSQL (Prisma) — Supabase: Dashboard → Settings → Database
# - Prefer "Connection pooling" session mode (port 5432) for Prisma migrations
# - If P1001 / IPv6 issues, use pooler host (e.g. …pooler.supabase.com:5432)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/avitan_dojo"

# Supabase — Dashboard → Settings → API (use your DEV project)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://YOUR_DEV_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="your-dev-anon-key"
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="your-dev-service-role-key"

# Password reset & absolute links — local dev
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION (set in Vercel / host — not in committed .env)
# =============================================================================
# Duplicate the same variable NAMES with PROD values:
#   DATABASE_URL              → prod Supabase Postgres connection string
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_*    → prod Supabase project URL + anon key
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY → prod service role (server-only)
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL       → https://your-app.vercel.app or custom domain
#
# Supabase (prod project): Auth → URL configuration must list this URL and
# redirect paths (/auth/*, reset-password, etc.).
#
# Vercel build (applies migrations then builds):
#   Build Command: npm run vercel-build
#
# Full checklist: docs/DEPLOYMENT.md

# Setup (dev DB): copy this file to .env, fill dev values, then:
#   npm run db:migrate
#   npm run db:seed
